In page 146, after line 36, to insert the following:
"Report on re-introduction of trade union tax relief
64. The Minister shall, within three months of the passing of this Act, prepare and lay before both Houses of the Oireachtas a report on—(a) the impact of trade union membership, based on comparative examples, statistics and case studies across a number of sectors, on—(i) income levels for employees;
(ii) reliance on working family payment;
(iii) the common good;
(iv) the achievement of Ireland's targets under the Sustainable Development Goals;
(v) the achievement of Ireland's UN and ILO commitments; and
(vi) the promotion of quality employment;
and(b) the options for the restoration on tax relief for trade union membership.".
